  "prompt": "I did really bad on my 1st term of 11th (cbse).If I pull myself together and do really well on the other 2 terms can I still get above 95% at the end?",
  "response": "The possibility depends on several factors:\n\n1. How badly you performed in the first term:\n- If your marks were significantly low, it will be challenging but not impossible\n- You'll need to score very high in the next two terms\n\n2. CBSE's final percentage calculation:\n- Typically involves averaging marks from all terms\n- Some weightage might be given to different terms\n\n3. Strategies to improve:\n- Create a comprehensive study plan\n- Get coaching/tuition if needed\n- Focus on understanding concepts\n- Practice previous years' question papers\n- Take regular mock tests\n- Manage time effectively\n\n4. Subject-wise approach:\n- Identify weak subjects\n- Focus more on subjects where you scored low\n- Seek help from teachers/tutors\n\n5. Realistic expectations:\n- Aiming for 95%+ will require dedicated effort\n- Consistent hard work is key\n- Start preparing immediately\n\nSuggestion:\n- Aim to score 90-95% in next two terms\n- This will help compensate for the first term's performance\n\nBottom line: With serious commitment and strategic preparation, you can significantly improve your overall percentage.\n\nWould you like specific advice on study techniques?",
